Sentencas: This paper investigates a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) with mixed-conducting electrodes.
Titulo: Numerical analysis of a planar anode-supported SOFC with composite electrodes

Sentencas: Direct internal methane reforming in the high-temperature cell is included.
Titulo: Numerical analysis of a planar anode-supported SOFC with composite electrodes

Sentencas: The numerical model used is three-dimensional, a single computational domain comprising the fuel and air channels and the electrodes-electrolyte assembly.
Titulo: Numerical analysis of a planar anode-supported SOFC with composite electrodes

Sentencas: The oxygen ion transport through the electrolyte is mimicked with an algorithm for Fickian diffusion built into the commercial computational package Star-CD.
Titulo: Numerical analysis of a planar anode-supported SOFC with composite electrodes

Sentencas: The equations describing transport, chemical and electrochemical processes for mass, momentum, species and energy are solved using Star-CD with in-house developed subroutines.
Titulo: Numerical analysis of a planar anode-supported SOFC with composite electrodes

Sentencas: Results for temperature, chemical species and current density distribution for co- and counter-flow configurations are shown and discussed.
Titulo: Numerical analysis of a planar anode-supported SOFC with composite electrodes

Sentencas: For co-flow, a sub-cooling effect manifests itself in the methane-rich region near the fuel entrance, while for counter-flow a super-heating effect manifests itself somewhat further downstream, where all the methane is consumed.
Titulo: Numerical analysis of a planar anode-supported SOFC with composite electrodes

Sentencas: Effects of varying air inlet conditions are also investigated.
Titulo: Numerical analysis of a planar anode-supported SOFC with composite electrodes
